The paper deals with the problem of secure distributed matrix multiplication, which is a topic related to cryptography and information theory. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial problems and coding theory, which are related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses polynomial codes, which are related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
